          <div class="font-normal text-md sm:text-lg md:text-xl lg:text-2xl">
            <p>Communities are the foundation of how we conserve and restore peatlands. Rural communities, including many indigenous peoples, depend on peatlands for agriculture, forestry, grazing and energy, and are the backbone of their local economies.</p>
<p>We aim to expand community-based peatland management across multiple landscapes by showcasing inspiring examples of successful local economies in peatlands to upscale finance, stimulate innovation, fill knowledge gaps and connect with global learning platforms to share knowledge, tools and experiences.</p>
